#31750
The Frjosa Hel-vegr Tundra~
   To the south and east, you can hear the loud roaring of the river.  The
snow is very deep and makes moving very difficult.  Everything is white and
cold here.  The expansive and cruel white abyss settles in one's soul as a
profound hopelessness.  You have exits in all four cardinal directions, all
lead to more snow except the south or east.  
~
