#31783
The Frjosa Hel-vegr Tundra~
   To the north, you can hear the loud roaring of the river.  The snow is very
deep and makes moving very difficult.  Everything is white and cold here.  
The expansive and cruel white abyss settles in one's soul like as a profound
hopelessness.  You have exits in all four cardinal directions and all lead to
more snow except the north.  
~
317 32768 0 0 0 13
D0
   You may jump into the river from this direction, however you will not be
able to come back up.  There is a long drop to the river and it is frozen
sheer cliff on either side of it.  
~
~
0 0 31835
D1
   Looking east, you cannot see much, except the white abyss that is this
horrible tundra.  There is a very good chance that the ground is unstable and
deadly thin.  One might say taking a step east would appear suicidal.  
~
