#31797
The Frjosa Hel-vegr Tundra~
   Looking in any direction proves to be pointless, as it is all white.  
Visibility is three to five feet at best.  The ground is frozen solid, the air
painfully dry and cold, and the wind feels like daggers.  This is no place for
any sane being.  Unless, you're a polar bear, you best find shelter and fire
soon.  Seems you've stumbled upon a solid patch of ground, this seems a bit
more stable than to the north or south.  Some faint remnants of extremely
large canine footprints are here.  
~
